main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Fairborn, Ohio on 30 October 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed using ground-radar and air-visual methods., The sighting lasted for 5 minutes., The object was described as possibly being a vehicle without running light but with a lighted cabin., There were a total of 2 observers present during the sighting., The report was submitted to O.I. for further analysis.
sighted object: possibly a vehicle without running light and with a lighted cabin
